OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FLargely dry
OL,6,Fat first but becoming cloudy through
OL,7,Fthe evening and overnight with some
OL,8,Fpatchy light rain for Deeside, staying
OL,9,Fdry in the north. Freshening southeast
OL,10,Fwinds around the coast.
OL,11,
OL,12,CWednesday:FLargely cloudy as bands of
OL,13,Frain push northeast in the morning.
OL,14,FTurning showery later, these showers
OL,15,Fheavy and thundery at times.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Thursday to Saturday:FSunny
OL,18,Fspells Thursday with a few showers
OL,19,Fpossible. A further rain band pushes
OL,20,Fnortheast on Friday. Bright spells and
OL,21,Fshowers again on Saturday.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
